"12oz. bottle served in an American pint. Pours a golden hue with a slightly hazy clarity and a rocky, two inch, bright white head. Nose is typical of a Belgian IPA - citrus, spice and zest. Taste follows nose - no surprises here. Mouthfeel is light-medium with a lively, slightly coarse carbonation and a mild acidity. Overall, a decent example of the style that I'm not generally a fan of. That said, I'm pleased to see Otter Creek expanding its portfolio"
