"I honestly do like the beer, but I just feel like it fell short on all the categories. It really is just OKAY - its good for Otter Creek, but I was expecting a lot more from them after having Citra Mantra on tap . The yeast/protein floaties I understand, but they are still just a turnoff for me. I would overlook them more if the beer packed more of a belgian punch, or an IPA punch for that matter. I do love the lemon curd flavor though, that comes through really nicely."
"this would be better without the belgian yeast, a jovially hopped pale pale ale, with a nice refreshing mouthfeel, but its muddled and bogged down by a lackluster belgian yeast expresison. blonde beer, looks wheat based, with a great big white head with excellent retention. the only problem is this snow globe yeast chunky wash swirling around in my glass. this looks like an old belgian strong ale that got lost in a cellar for awhile, its almost gross how much there is, seems not necessary to me. the nose is hops first, lemony and light, but they are covered up by the melon and banana esters of this yeast strain. the flavor is just like the smell, hops first, yeast interrupts and carries on in isolation. very light malt base, and a potentially very refreshing beer in hot weather, but the intensity of the yeast covers up how well and interestingly hopped the beer is, and all the sediment is sort of unappetizing. still, its obviously well made stuff with a unique interaction between yeast and hops, and probably deserves a little more credit than i am giving it with this review. its something different from the masses, and is absolutely worth trying."
