"O: Another great beer from CBC and Brewmaster Mike Gerhart. I feel like the name White IPA is misleading a bit, but that is about it. This is a great beer that isn't hoppy at all, at least not to my palate."
"Poured into a bell tulip, a cloudy, golden-yellow color with a finger of frothy white head that settled to a foamy layer; good retention and lacing. In the nose, Belgian yeast and coriander came at me first, bready malts and light citrus zest followed. This brew really came off more as a witbier to me, but I guess it was hoppy enough to be considered a BIPA. As in the aroma, I got a lot of yeast and spice in the taste, coriander, orange peel, light crisp hops that were present, but never really reached over the dominating ""wit"" character. Medium body, and nice drinkability. Overall, this was a good brew, but I probably wouldn't get it again unless there were no better options available to me."
